{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1446c316-e283-426b-b8c8-30797339eb80","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed first.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_dz9P8JXxbYZCzk6U0nDneV","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-3c24c5e9627c4381bcf708e9f5c47041/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-3c24c5e9627c4381bcf708e9f5c47041/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"3597edad-2246-4876-9af4-fb8ffe6f0dbc","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` has `open BrokenOrder.Domain`, meaning it depends on `Domain.fs`. So `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs` in the compile order.\n\nThe fix is to reorder the `<Compile>` items so that `Domain.fs` comes first, then `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":462,"requestId":"5BE6:1F0E10:48CEEC8:505A91D:69F9E5E9"},"id":"63cbaf75-7963-4323-a807-9e15db589966","timestamp":"2026-05-05T12:43:31.103Z","parentId":"cab41aa7-9448-4a7a-aad7-972a080b7636"}
